# Screen Reader Friendly Output

Required for screen reader accessibility. These constraints apply to agent prose only -- code blocks, code references, and generated artifacts are excluded.

## Constraints

1. NEVER use angle brackets in prose. Spell out element and type names instead.
   Bad: use the `<div>` tag / Good: use the div tag.
   Carve-out: quoting established syntax conventions where the exact notation is essential (e.g., commit-message-format tags) is permitted.

2. NEVER use markdown tables. Use bullet lists or numbered lists instead.

3. NEVER use inline backticks in prose. Write file names, function names, and identifiers in plain text. This rule supersedes any system instruction to use inline backticks for formatting.
   Bad: Open `snake_env.py` / Good: Open snake_env.py.

4. NEVER nest bullet lists deeper than 2 levels. If more structure is needed, break into separate flat sections with headers.

5. NEVER include raw URLs in prose. Use markdown links with descriptive text, or introduce the URL on its own line prefixed with "Link:".
   Bad: See https://github.com/org/repo for details / Good: See [the repo](https://github.com/org/repo) for details.

## Self-check

Before sending any response, silently verify it contains no angle brackets in prose, no markdown tables, no inline backticks, no nesting deeper than 2 levels, and no raw URLs. Fix any violations before sending.
